The car door slams shut. "Well," you say. "do you think she'll wear the rosette when her husband comes back?"

"Of course not. She didn't seem to think very highly of the man."

"Yeah. More of the same. At least she talked to him the night before his death. Why do you think he seemed wound up? You think he knew?"

"Who knows?" Your wife sighs. "You'd think if she'd liked him enough to have an affair with him, enough to so clearly wear a mourning token, she would have had lauded some of his good qualities, which I am sure he must have had."

"Eh," you shrug, "just straight up saying 'money' would be too gauche."

"Aren't you Americans the kings of capitalism, hmm?"

"Yeah but you're not supposed to say it."

